editorialSummary.text: Year-round farmer's market, open on certain days, with various farm & small batch food producers.

originalText.text:
Stumbled on this little market on my way to the river!

There are about 10 or so vendors - most selling fresh vegetables, fruits, and flowers, with a few stands selling cheese and fish as well. It‚Äôs very cute and has a good amount of options for its size and given the neighborhood.

Not very crowded when I went. Would recommend to check out if you live in the area and want to support local vendors!

originalText.text:
Great little farmers market that runs seasonally and is finally back. It doesn't tend to get too busy and is nice and quiet in the mornings. Usually there's a fish stand, which wasn't there today (hopefully it will return this year). There's also a baked goods stand and one that sells dairy-products and eggs. There's several fresh produce stands.

The prices for produce can differ quite a bit depending on the stand. I bought some produce at the stand that tends to be at the corner and has a big "ORGANIC" sign today. The prices were extremely steep comparatively ($12 for three smallish yukon gold potatoes and three green garlic bulbs üò±). While it's nice to have an organic option, I'll be buying from the other produce stands.
